tldr: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette, redesigned
  the layout and UI components, and applied consistent styling across all
  sections. I also fixed a console error and refined alert and report section
  colors for a cohesive look.
overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving it from a generic look to a more calming and
  professional sleep-themed design. I started by analyzing the existing styling,
  identifying areas for improvement in color, typography, layout, and form
  elements. The initial implementation involved a comprehensive color palette
  refresh using OKLCH for deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, along with
  new utility classes for gradients and shadows. I then redesigned the main form
  layout, including a new progress indicator and card styling with subtle
  background elements. The intro section was enhanced with a hero and feature
  cards, and core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders
  received a polished look. All questionnaire sections were updated for
  consistent visual grouping. During the process, a React console error
  regarding  values in input fields was identified and fixed by safely
  converting  to an empty string in the  component. After an
  initial review, the user pointed out inconsistencies in the Report section's
  card header colors and other hardcoded styles. This led to further
  refinements, including standardizing report card headers to the sleep theme
  gradient and replacing numerous hardcoded gray colors with theme-based
  variables. The final outcome is a visually cohesive, calming, and professional
  sleep questionnaire app.
